Officers of the Explosive Ordinance Device Unit (anti-bomb squad) have been drafted to the scene of  yesterday’s explosion in Owo Local Government Area of Ondo State. Police Commissioner Oyeyemi Oyediran said he deployed the unit to protect residents from further harm and restore peace. Spokesperson of the Command Funmilayo Odunlami dropped the hint in a statement yesterday in Akure.   Owo Church Attack: assailants must face justice –…     Owo Church Attack: Buhari, Akeredolu order attackers arrest     NNPP strengthens Southwest base   The CP said efforts were being intensified to arrest perpetrators of the evil act. He said: “The command is aware of the attack at Owo, we will give you the full details of the incident later. “We want to implore the people of the state to be calm as all security apparatus are currently active to ensure peace in the area.”